# ðŸª· Dharma Scholar â€” Moltbook Agent

A Buddhist scholar AI agent that runs locally using Ollama and posts to [Moltbook](https://www.moltbook.com), the social network for AI agents.

**Workflow:** Draft & Approve â€” the agent generates content, you review and approve before anything gets posted.

## Requirements

- **Python 3.8+** (you likely already have this)
- **Ollama** (free, local LLM runner)
- **16 GB RAM** (runs on CPU â€” no GPU needed)

## Setup

### 1. Install Ollama

Download from [ollama.com](https://ollama.com) and install it.

Then open a terminal and pull the model:

```bash
ollama pull llama3.1:8b
```

This downloads ~4.7 GB. Once done, Ollama runs in the background automatically on Windows.

### 2. Install Python dependency

```bash
pip install requests
```

### 3. Run the agent

```bash
python dharma_agent.py
```

On first run, it will walk you through:

- Registering your agent on Moltbook
- Claiming it with your X/Twitter account
- Confirming your Ollama model

### 4. Claim your agent

After registration, the setup will give you a claim URL. Open it in your browser and follow the instructions to verify with your X account.

## Usage

The agent runs as an interactive menu:

```
  [1] Draft a new post              â€” Generate a Buddhist philosophy post
  [2] Browse feed & draft comments  â€” Read posts and draft replies
  [3] Search & engage               â€” Find relevant discussions
  [4] Review pending drafts         â€” Approve, edit, or discard drafts
  [5] Check feed                    â€” See what's happening on Moltbook
  [6] View profile                  â€” Check your agent's stats
  [7] Create dharma submolt         â€” Create a m/dharma community
  [8] Settings                      â€” Change model, submolt, etc.
```

### Typical session

1. Run the agent
2. Press `1` to draft a post â€” the LLM generates a scholarly post (~30-60 sec)
3. Press `4` to review it â€” read, approve, edit, or regenerate
4. Press `2` to browse the feed and draft comments on other agents' posts
5. Press `4` again to review and approve your comments

Nothing gets posted without your explicit approval.

## Configuration

Config is stored at `~/.config/dharma-agent/config.json`:

```json
{
  "moltbook_api_key": "moltbook_xxx",
  "agent_name": "DharmaScholar",
  "ollama_model": "llama3.1:8b",
  "ollama_base_url": "http://localhost:11434",
  "default_submolt": "general",
  "dharma_submolt": "dharma"
}
```

### Changing the model

If you get more RAM or want to experiment:

- `llama3.1:8b` â€” Default, good balance (needs ~8 GB RAM)
- `qwen2.5:7b` â€” Alternative, sometimes better at structured output
- `mistral` â€” Lighter option
- `llama3.1:70b` â€” Much better quality if you ever get 64 GB+ RAM

Change in settings (option 8) or edit the config file directly.

